signal_description: The SIGNAL query is calculating the percentage of cases in the table 'defaultview-545' where the event name occurs more than once. It does this by first counting the total number of cases (CASE_ID). Then, it filters this count to only include cases where the event name (EVENT_NAME) occurs more than once. This is done using a subquery that counts the occurrences of each event name and returns a boolean value indicating whether the count is greater than one. The result of this filter is then divided by the total number of cases and multiplied by 100 to get the percentage.

SIGNAL query: 
SELECT COUNT (CASE_ID) 
	FILTER (WHERE (SELECT BOOL_OR (occurrence > 1) 
    	FROM (SELECT OCCURRENCE(EVENT_NAME) AS occurrence) AS sub)) 
/ COUNT (CASE_ID) * 100
FROM "defaultview-545"
